{
  "page": "Rolland Storm",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Ser</span><br />Rolland Storm<br /><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> the Bastard of Nightsong</span></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Rolland_Storm_by_Lu.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Rolland Storm by Lu.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a6/Rolland_Storm_by_Lu.png/350px-Rolland_Storm_by_Lu.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"438\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a6/Rolland_Storm_by_Lu.png/525px-Rolland_Storm_by_Lu.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a6/Rolland_Storm_by_Lu.png/700px-Rolland_Storm_by_Lu.png 2x\" /></a><div>Rolland Storm by lupotterdraws ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nThe Bastard of Nightsong<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Castellan\" title=\"Castellan\">Castellan</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Nightsong\" title=\"Lord of Nightsong\">Lord of Nightsong</a> (claimant)<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Marches\" title=\"Lord of the Marches\">Lord of the Marches</a> (claimant)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Caron\" title=\"House Caron\">House Caron</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Baratheon_of_Dragonstone\" title=\"House Baratheon of Dragonstone\">House Baratheon of Dragonstone</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dornish_Marches\" title=\"Dornish Marches\">Marcher</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dornish_Marches\" title=\"Dornish Marches\">Dornish Marches</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafrolland_storm.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafrolland_storm.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/Bryen_Caron\" title=\"Bryen Caron\">Bryen Caron</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">Personal arms</span></th><td>\nNo known personal arms<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (appendix)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appendix)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Rolland Storm</b>, called <b>the Bastard of Nightsong</b>, is a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Caron\" title=\"House Caron\">House Caron</a>. He is the <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> son of the late <a href=\"/index.php/Bryen_Caron\" title=\"Bryen Caron\">Bryen Caron</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Nightsong\" title=\"Lord of Nightsong\">Lord of Nightsong</a>, and is the half-brother of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Bryce_Caron\" title=\"Bryce Caron\">Bryce Caron</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolland_Storm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Rolland_Storm\" title=\"Category:Images of Rolland Storm\">Images of Rolland Storm</a></div>\n<p>Rolland's face is covered in scars from the <a href=\"/index.php/Pox\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pox\">pox</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Rolland Storm worships <a href=\"/index.php/Warrior_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Warrior (the Seven)\">the Warrior</a>, an aspect of the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a>, with a faith as fierce as he is.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> considers him a seasoned killer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> both consider Rolland to be a good and loyal man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Rolland gives off an \"air of tattered chivalry\", according to Davos.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolland_Storm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolland_Storm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Bastard_of_Nightsong_unknown.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c8/The_Bastard_of_Nightsong_unknown.png/350px-The_Bastard_of_Nightsong_unknown.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"222\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/c8/The_Bastard_of_Nightsong_unknown.png/525px-The_Bastard_of_Nightsong_unknown.png 1.5x, /images/c/c8/The_Bastard_of_Nightsong_unknown.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Bastard_of_Nightsong_unknown.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Bastard of Nightsong, by Jorge Maese © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>Ser Rolland joined his true born half-brother, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Bryce_Caron\" title=\"Bryce Caron\">Bryce Caron</a>, in declaring first for <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a> at the outset of the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a> and then <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> after Renly's assassination at <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Storm%27s_End_(299)\" title=\"Siege of Storm&#39;s End (299)\">Storm's End</a>. Rolland commanded the rearguard after the disastrous end to the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>, allowing Stannis to reach the safety of <a href=\"/index.php/Salladhor_Saan\" title=\"Salladhor Saan\">Salladhor Saan</a>'s fleet and escape to <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>. Lord Bryce, however, was killed in the fighting by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Philip_Foote\" title=\"Philip Foote\">Philip Foote</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> rewarded Philip with the lands, rights, and incomes of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Caron\" title=\"House Caron\">House Caron</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Rolland is among the <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_men\" title=\"King&#39;s men\">king's men</a>, those Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a> seeks out who are still loyal to Stannis without being believers in the new faith, the <a href=\"/index.php/R%27hllor\" title=\"R&#39;hllor\">Lord of Light</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> He is part of Davos's plot to send <a href=\"/index.php/Edric_Storm\" title=\"Edric Storm\">Edric Storm</a> away from <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>. The Bastard of Nightsong is the only conspirator who remains with Lord Davos at Dragonstone after Edric's escape, and he keeps watch over some guardsmen as Davos confronts King Stannis and his <a href=\"/index.php/Red_priest\" title=\"Red priest\">red priestess</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Melisandre\" title=\"Melisandre\">Melisandre</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Once at the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>, Stannis sends word to Rolland, the new <a href=\"/index.php/Castellan\" title=\"Castellan\">castellan</a> of Dragonstone, to begin mining <a href=\"/index.php/Obsidian\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Obsidian\">obsidian</a> from the tunnels underneath the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonmont\" title=\"Dragonmont\">Dragonmont</a>, as the king hopes to use dragonglass against the <a href=\"/index.php/Others\" title=\"Others\">Others</a>. Stannis thinks Dragonstone will not be be able to hold out for long, however.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos78.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos78.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolland_Storm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rolland_Storm_by_cloudninja9.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/83/Rolland_Storm_by_cloudninja9.jpg/350px-Rolland_Storm_by_cloudninja9.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"490\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/83/Rolland_Storm_by_cloudninja9.jpg/525px-Rolland_Storm_by_cloudninja9.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/83/Rolland_Storm_by_cloudninja9.jpg/700px-Rolland_Storm_by_cloudninja9.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rolland_Storm_by_cloudninja9.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Rolland Storm, by cloudninja9 ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Ser Rolland commands the small garrison Stannis left to hold Dragonstone after he sailed north. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Paxter_Redwyne\" title=\"Paxter Redwyne\">Paxter Redwyne</a> is sent to besiege Dragonstone to appease the Queen Regent, <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a>, and nullify the closest threat to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. After the <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_the_Shields\" title=\"Taking of the Shields\">taking of the Shields</a> by <a href=\"/index.php/Euron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Euron Greyjoy\">Euron Greyjoy</a>, however, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Loras_Tyrell\" title=\"Loras Tyrell\">Loras Tyrell</a> begs to take command so that the <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Dragonstone\" title=\"Siege of Dragonstone\">siege of Dragonstone</a> can be concluded, allowing the <a href=\"/index.php/Redwyne_fleet\" title=\"Redwyne fleet\">Redwyne fleet</a> to return to the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a> and defend their homelands from the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Aurane_Waters\" title=\"Aurane Waters\">Aurane Waters</a> later reports to Cersei that upon arrival at Dragonstone, Loras offered Rolland single combat, which was declined. The resulting assault cost more than a thousand lives and severely injured Loras, but Rolland was unable to hold the keep and Dragonstone was finally taken by the Iron Throne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Rolland's status after the assault is unknown.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolland_Storm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Rolland is considered the pretender <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Nightsong\" title=\"Lord of Nightsong\">Lord of Nightsong</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> as the title had been granted by the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannisters</a> to Philip Foote.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolland_Storm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The Bastard of Nightsong had a pox-ravaged face and an air of tattered chivalry; Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gerald_Gower\" title=\"Gerald Gower\">Gerald Gower</a> was broad, bluff, and blond; Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Andrew_Estermont\" title=\"Andrew Estermont\">Andrew Estermont</a> stood a head taller, with a spade-shaped beard and shaggy brown eye-brows. They were all good men in their own ways, Davos thought.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The pox-scarred bastard that <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis</a> had left to hold <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">his castle</a> was no callow <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney\" title=\"Tourney\">tourney</a> champion but a seasoned killer. If <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">the gods</a> were good, he would give Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Loras_Tyrell\" title=\"Loras Tyrell\">Loras</a> the glorious end he seemed to want.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rolland_Storm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Unknown</td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dashed black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dashed black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dashed black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dashed black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dashed black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font: